==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scotticism
<hw>Scot"ti*cism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An idiom, or mode
of expression, peculiar to Scotland or Scotchmen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That, in short, in which the <qex>Scotticism</qex> of Scotsmen
most intimately consists, is the habit of emphasis.</q>
<rj><qau>Masson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scotticize</ent>⟦br⟧
